import Mathlib.Topology.UniformSpace.UniformConvergence
import Mathlib.Topology.UniformSpace.Pi
import Mathlib.Topology.UniformSpace.Equiv
import Mathlib.Topology.RestrictGen

/-!
# Topology and uniform structure of uniform convergence

This files endows `Оұ вҶ’ ОІ` with the topologies / uniform structures of
- uniform convergence on `Оұ`
- uniform convergence on a specified family `рқ”–` of sets of `Оұ`, also called `рқ”–`-convergence

Since `Оұ вҶ’ ОІ` is already endowed with the topologies and uniform structures of pointwise
convergence, we introduce type aliases `UniformFun Оұ ОІ` (denoted `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ`) and
`UniformOnFun Оұ ОІ рқ”–` (denoted `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ`) and we actually endow *these* with the structures
of uniform and `рқ”–`-convergence respectively.

Usual examples of the second construction include :
- the topology of compact convergence, when `рқ”–` is the set of compacts of `Оұ`
- the strong topology on the dual of a topological vector space (TVS) `E`, when `рқ”–` is the set of
  Von Neumann bounded subsets of `E`
- the weak-* topology on the dual of a TVS `E`, when `рқ”–` is the set of singletons of `E`.

This file contains a lot of technical facts, so it is heavily commented, proofs included!

## Main definitions

* `UniformFun.gen`: basis sets for the uniformity of uniform convergence. These are sets
  of the form `S(V) := {(f, g) | вҲҖ x : Оұ, (f x, g x) вҲҲ V}` for some `V : Set (ОІ Г— ОІ)`
* `UniformFun.uniformSpace`: uniform structure of uniform convergence. This is the
  `UniformSpace` on `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ` whose uniformity is generated by the sets `S(V)` for `V вҲҲ рқ“Ө ОІ`.
  We will denote this uniform space as `рқ’°(Оұ, ОІ, uОІ)`, both in the comments and as a local notation
  in the Lean code, where `uОІ` is the uniform space structure on `ОІ`.
  This is declared as an instance on `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ`.
* `UniformOnFun.uniformSpace`: uniform structure of `рқ”–`-convergence, where
  `рқ”– : Set (Set Оұ)`. This is the infimum, for `S вҲҲ рқ”–`, of the pullback of `рқ’° S ОІ` by the map of
  restriction to `S`. We will denote it `рқ’ұ(Оұ, ОІ, рқ”–, uОІ)`, where `uОІ` is the uniform space structure
  on `ОІ`.
  This is declared as an instance on `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ`.

## Main statements

### Basic properties

* `UniformFun.uniformContinuous_eval`: evaluation is uniformly continuous on `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ`.
* `UniformFun.t2Space`: the topology of uniform convergence on `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ` is TвӮӮ if
  `ОІ` is TвӮӮ.
* `UniformFun.tendsto_iff_tendstoUniformly`: `рқ’°(Оұ, ОІ, uОІ)` is
  indeed the uniform structure of uniform convergence
* `UniformOnFun.uniformContinuous_eval_of_mem`: evaluation at a point contained in a
  set of `рқ”–` is uniformly continuous on `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ`
* `UniformOnFun.t2Space_of_covering`: the topology of `рқ”–`-convergence on `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ` is TвӮӮ if
  `ОІ` is TвӮӮ and `рқ”–` covers `Оұ`
* `UniformOnFun.tendsto_iff_tendstoUniformlyOn`:
  `рқ’ұ(Оұ, ОІ, рқ”– uОІ)` is indeed the uniform structure of `рқ”–`-convergence

### Functoriality and compatibility with product of uniform spaces

In order to avoid the need for filter bases as much as possible when using these definitions,
we develop an extensive API for manipulating these structures abstractly. As usual in the topology
section of mathlib, we first state results about the complete lattices of `UniformSpace`s on
fixed types, and then we use these to deduce categorical-like results about maps between two
uniform spaces.

We only describe these in the harder case of `рқ”–`-convergence, as the names of the corresponding
results for uniform convergence can easily be guessed.

#### Order statements

* `UniformOnFun.mono`: let `uвӮҒ`, `uвӮӮ` be two uniform structures on `Оі` and
  `рқ”–вӮҒ рқ”–вӮӮ : Set (Set Оұ)`. If `uвӮҒ вүӨ uвӮӮ` and `рқ”–вӮӮ вҠҶ рқ”–вӮҒ` then `рқ’ұ(Оұ, Оі, рқ”–вӮҒ, uвӮҒ) вүӨ рқ’ұ(Оұ, Оі, рқ”–вӮӮ, uвӮӮ)`.
* `UniformOnFun.iInf_eq`: if `u` is a family of uniform structures on `Оі`, then
  `рқ’ұ(Оұ, Оі, рқ”–, (вЁ… i, u i)) = вЁ… i, рқ’ұ(Оұ, Оі, рқ”–, u i)`.
* `UniformOnFun.comap_eq`: if `u` is a uniform structures on `ОІ` and `f : Оі вҶ’ ОІ`, then
  `рқ’ұ(Оұ, Оі, рқ”–, comap f u) = comap (fun g вҶҰ f вҲҳ g) рқ’ұ(Оұ, Оі, рқ”–, uвӮҒ)`.

An interesting note about these statements is that they are proved without ever unfolding the basis
definition of the uniform structure of uniform convergence! Instead, we build a
(not very interesting) Galois connection `UniformFun.gc` and then rely on the Galois
connection API to do most of the work.

#### Morphism statements (unbundled)

* `UniformOnFun.postcomp_uniformContinuous`: if `f : Оі вҶ’ ОІ` is uniformly
  continuous, then `(fun g вҶҰ f вҲҳ g) : (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] Оі) вҶ’ (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ)` is uniformly continuous.
* `UniformOnFun.postcomp_isUniformInducing`: if `f : Оі вҶ’ ОІ` is a uniform
  inducing, then `(fun g вҶҰ f вҲҳ g) : (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] Оі) вҶ’ (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ)` is a uniform inducing.
* `UniformOnFun.precomp_uniformContinuous`: let `f : Оі вҶ’ Оұ`, `рқ”– : Set (Set Оұ)`,
  `рқ”— : Set (Set Оі)`, and assume that `вҲҖ T вҲҲ рқ”—, f '' T вҲҲ рқ”–`. Then, the function
  `(fun g вҶҰ g вҲҳ f) : (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ) вҶ’ (Оі вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”—] ОІ)` is uniformly continuous.

#### Isomorphism statements (bundled)

* `UniformOnFun.congrRight`: turn a uniform isomorphism `Оі вүғбөӨ ОІ` into a uniform isomorphism
  `(Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] Оі) вүғбөӨ (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ)` by post-composing.
* `UniformOnFun.congrLeft`: turn a bijection `e : Оі вүғ Оұ` such that we have both
  `вҲҖ T вҲҲ рқ”—, e '' T вҲҲ рқ”–` and `вҲҖ S вҲҲ рқ”–, e вҒ»В№' S вҲҲ рқ”—` into a uniform isomorphism
  `(Оі вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”—] ОІ) вүғбөӨ (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] ОІ)` by pre-composing.
* `UniformOnFun.uniformEquivPiComm`: the natural bijection between `Оұ вҶ’ О  i, Оҙ i`
  and `О  i, Оұ вҶ’ Оҙ i`, upgraded to a uniform isomorphism between `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] (О  i, Оҙ i)` and
  `О  i, Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] Оҙ i`.

#### Important use cases

* If `G` is a uniform group, then `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] G` is a uniform group: since `(/) : G Г— G вҶ’ G` is
  uniformly continuous, `UniformOnFun.postcomp_uniformContinuous` tells us that
  `((/) вҲҳ вҖ”) : (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] G Г— G) вҶ’ (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] G)` is uniformly continuous. By precomposing with
  `UniformOnFun.uniformEquivProdArrow`, this gives that
  `(/) : (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] G) Г— (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] G) вҶ’ (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ[рқ”–] G)` is also uniformly continuous
* The transpose of a continuous linear map is continuous for the strong topologies: since
  continuous linear maps are uniformly continuous and map bounded sets to bounded sets,
  this is just a special case of `UniformOnFun.precomp_uniformContinuous`.

