variable (Оұ ОІ : Type*) {Оі О№ : Type*}
variable {p : Filter О№}

/-- Basis sets for the uniformity of uniform convergence: `gen Оұ ОІ V` is the set of pairs `(f, g)`
of functions `Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ` such that `вҲҖ x, (f x, g x) вҲҲ V`. -/
protected def gen (V : Set (ОІ Г— ОІ)) : Set ((Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ) Г— (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ)) :=
  { uv : (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ) Г— (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ) | вҲҖ x, (toFun uv.1 x, toFun uv.2 x) вҲҲ V }

/-- If `рқ“•` is a filter on `ОІ Г— ОІ`, then the set of all `UniformFun.gen Оұ ОІ V` for
`V вҲҲ рқ“•` is a filter basis on `(Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ) Г— (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ)`. This will only be applied to `рқ“• = рқ“Ө ОІ` when
`ОІ` is equipped with a `UniformSpace` structure, but it is useful to define it for any filter in
order to be able to state that it has a lower adjoint (see `UniformFun.gc`). -/
protected theorem isBasis_gen (рқ“‘ : Filter <| ОІ Г— ОІ) :
    IsBasis (fun V : Set (ОІ Г— ОІ) => V вҲҲ рқ“‘) (UniformFun.gen Оұ ОІ) :=
  вҹЁвҹЁuniv, univ_memвҹ©, @fun U V hU hV =>
    вҹЁU вҲ© V, inter_mem hU hV, fun _ huv => вҹЁfun x => (huv x).left, fun x => (huv x).rightвҹ©вҹ©вҹ©

/-- For `рқ“• : Filter (ОІ Г— ОІ)`, this is the set of all `UniformFun.gen Оұ ОІ V` for
`V вҲҲ рқ“•` as a bundled `FilterBasis` over `(Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ) Г— (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ)`. This will only be applied to
`рқ“• = рқ“Ө ОІ` when `ОІ` is equipped with a `UniformSpace` structure, but it is useful to define it for
any filter in order to be able to state that it has a lower adjoint
(see `UniformFun.gc`). -/
protected def basis (рқ“• : Filter <| ОІ Г— ОІ) : FilterBasis ((Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ) Г— (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ)) :=
  (UniformFun.isBasis_gen Оұ ОІ рқ“•).filterBasis

/-- For `рқ“• : Filter (ОІ Г— ОІ)`, this is the filter generated by the filter basis
`UniformFun.basis Оұ ОІ рқ“•`. For `рқ“• = рқ“Ө ОІ`, this will be the uniformity of uniform
convergence on `Оұ`. -/
protected def filter (рқ“• : Filter <| ОІ Г— ОІ) : Filter ((Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ) Г— (Оұ вҶ’бөӨ ОІ)) :=
  (UniformFun.basis Оұ ОІ рқ“•).filter

